  16 module: vmware_guest
  17 short_description: Manages virtual machines in vCenter
  18 description: >
  19    This module can be used to create new virtual machines from templates or other virtual machines,
  20    manage power state of virtual machine such as power on, power off, suspend, shutdown, reboot, restart etc.,
  21    modify various virtual machine components like network, disk, customization etc.,
  22    rename a virtual machine and remove a virtual machine with associated components.
  23 version_added: '2.2'
  24 author:
  25 - Loic Blot (@nerzhul) <loic.blot@unix-experience.fr>
  26 - Philippe Dellaert (@pdellaert) <philippe@dellaert.org>
  27 - Abhijeet Kasurde (@Akasurde) <akasurde@redhat.com>
  28 requirements:
  29 - python >= 2.6
  30 - PyVmomi
  31 notes:
  32     - Please make sure that the user used for M(vmware_guest) has the correct level of privileges.
  33     - For example, following is the list of minimum privileges required by users to create virtual machines.
  34     - "   DataStore > Allocate Space"
  35     - "   Virtual Machine > Configuration > Add New Disk"
  36     - "   Virtual Machine > Configuration > Add or Remove Device"
  37     - "   Virtual Machine > Inventory > Create New"
  38     - "   Network > Assign Network"
  39     - "   Resource > Assign Virtual Machine to Resource Pool"
  40     - "Module may require additional privileges as well, which may be required for gathering facts - e.g. ESXi configurations."
  41     - Tested on vSphere 5.5, 6.0, 6.5 and 6.7.
  42     - Use SCSI disks instead of IDE when you want to expand online disks by specifying a SCSI controller.
  43     - Uses SysPrep for Windows VM (depends on 'guest_id' parameter match 'win') with PyVmomi.
  44     - In order to change the VM's parameters (e.g. number of CPUs), the VM must be powered off unless the hot-add
  45       support is enabled and the C(state=present) must be used to apply the changes.
  46     - "For additional information please visit Ansible VMware community wiki - U(https://github.com/ansible/community/wiki/VMware)."

 683     def __init__(self, module):
 684         self.module = module
 685         self.next_disk_unit_number = 0
 686         self.scsi_device_type = {
 687             'lsilogic': vim.vm.device.VirtualLsiLogicController,
 688             'paravirtual': vim.vm.device.ParaVirtualSCSIController,
 689             'buslogic': vim.vm.device.VirtualBusLogicController,
 690             'lsilogicsas': vim.vm.device.VirtualLsiLogicSASController,
 691         }

 693     def create_scsi_controller(self, scsi_type):
 694         scsi_ctl = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()
 695         scsi_ctl.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.add
 696         scsi_device = self.scsi_device_type.get(scsi_type, vim.vm.device.ParaVirtualSCSIController)
 697         scsi_ctl.device = scsi_device()
 698         scsi_ctl.device.busNumber = 0
 699         # While creating a new SCSI controller, temporary key value
 700         # should be unique negative integers
 701         scsi_ctl.device.key = -randint(1000, 9999)
 702         scsi_ctl.device.hotAddRemove = True
 703         scsi_ctl.device.sharedBus = 'noSharing'
 704         scsi_ctl.device.scsiCtlrUnitNumber = 7
 705 
 706         return scsi_ctl

 708     def is_scsi_controller(self, device):
 709         return isinstance(device, tuple(self.scsi_device_type.values()))

 711     @staticmethod
 712     def create_ide_controller(bus_number=0):
 713         ide_ctl = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()

 715         ide_ctl.device = vim.vm.device.VirtualIDEController()

 717         # While creating a new IDE controller, temporary key value

 720         ide_ctl.device.busNumber = bus_number

 724     @staticmethod
 725     def create_cdrom(ide_device, cdrom_type, iso_path=None, unit_number=0):
 726         cdrom_spec = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()
 727         cdrom_spec.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.add
 728         cdrom_spec.device = vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom()
 729         cdrom_spec.device.controllerKey = ide_device.key
 730         cdrom_spec.device.key = -randint(3000, 3999)
 731         cdrom_spec.device.unitNumber = unit_number
 732         cdrom_spec.device.connectable = vim.vm.device.VirtualDevice.ConnectInfo()
 733         cdrom_spec.device.connectable.allowGuestControl = True
 734         cdrom_spec.device.connectable.startConnected = (cdrom_type != "none")
 735         if cdrom_type in ["none", "client"]:
 736             cdrom_spec.device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom.RemotePassthroughBackingInfo()
 737         elif cdrom_type == "iso":
 738             cdrom_spec.device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom.IsoBackingInfo(fileName=iso_path)
 739 
 740         return cdrom_spec

 742     @staticmethod
 743     def is_equal_cdrom(vm_obj, cdrom_device, cdrom_type, iso_path):
 744         if cdrom_type == "none":
 745             return (isinstance(cdrom_device.backing, vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom.RemotePassthroughBackingInfo) and
 746                     cdrom_device.connectable.allowGuestControl and
 747                     not cdrom_device.connectable.startConnected and
 748                     (vm_obj.runtime.powerState != vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn or not cdrom_device.connectable.connected))
 749         elif cdrom_type == "client":
 750             return (isinstance(cdrom_device.backing, vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom.RemotePassthroughBackingInfo) and
 751                     cdrom_device.connectable.allowGuestControl and
 752                     cdrom_device.connectable.startConnected and
 753                     (vm_obj.runtime.powerState != vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn or cdrom_device.connectable.connected))
 754         elif cdrom_type == "iso":
 755             return (isinstance(cdrom_device.backing, vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom.IsoBackingInfo) and
 756                     cdrom_device.backing.fileName == iso_path and
 757                     cdrom_device.connectable.allowGuestControl and
 758                     cdrom_device.connectable.startConnected and
 759                     (vm_obj.runtime.powerState != vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn or cdrom_device.connectable.connected))

 761     @staticmethod
 762     def update_cdrom_config(vm_obj, cdrom_spec, cdrom_device, iso_path=None):
 763         # Updating an existing CD-ROM
 764         if cdrom_spec["type"] in ["client", "none"]:
 765             cdrom_device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom.RemotePassthroughBackingInfo()
 766         elif cdrom_spec["type"] == "iso" and iso_path is not None:
 767             cdrom_device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualCdrom.IsoBackingInfo(fileName=iso_path)
 768         cdrom_device.connectable = vim.vm.device.VirtualDevice.ConnectInfo()
 769         cdrom_device.connectable.allowGuestControl = True
 770         cdrom_device.connectable.startConnected = (cdrom_spec["type"] != "none")
 771         if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn:
 772             cdrom_device.connectable.connected = (cdrom_spec["type"] != "none")

 774     def remove_cdrom(self, cdrom_device):
 775         cdrom_spec = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()

 777         cdrom_spec.device = cdrom_device

 781     def create_scsi_disk(self, scsi_ctl, disk_index=None):
 782         diskspec = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()
 783         diskspec.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.add
 784         diskspec.device = vim.vm.device.VirtualDisk()
 785         diskspec.device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualDisk.FlatVer2BackingInfo()
 786         diskspec.device.controllerKey = scsi_ctl.device.key
 787 
 788         if self.next_disk_unit_number == 7:
 789             raise AssertionError()
 790         if disk_index == 7:
 791             raise AssertionError()
 792         """
 793         Configure disk unit number.
 794         """
 795         if disk_index is not None:
 796             diskspec.device.unitNumber = disk_index
 797             self.next_disk_unit_number = disk_index + 1
 798         else:
 799             diskspec.device.unitNumber = self.next_disk_unit_number
 800             self.next_disk_unit_number += 1
 801 
 802         # unit number 7 is reserved to SCSI controller, increase next index
 803         if self.next_disk_unit_number == 7:
 804             self.next_disk_unit_number += 1
 805 
 806         return diskspec

 808     def get_device(self, device_type, name):
 809         nic_dict = dict(pcnet32=vim.vm.device.VirtualPCNet32(),
 810                         vmxnet2=vim.vm.device.VirtualVmxnet2(),
 811                         vmxnet3=vim.vm.device.VirtualVmxnet3(),
 812                         e1000=vim.vm.device.VirtualE1000(),
 813                         e1000e=vim.vm.device.VirtualE1000e(),
 814                         sriov=vim.vm.device.VirtualSriovEthernetCard(),
 815                         )
 816         if device_type in nic_dict:
 817             return nic_dict[device_type]
 818         else:
 819             self.module.fail_json(msg='Invalid device_type "%s"'
 820                                       ' for network "%s"' % (device_type, name))

 822     def create_nic(self, device_type, device_label, device_infos):
 823         nic = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()

 826         nic.device.deviceInfo = vim.Description()

 829         nic.device.connectable = vim.vm.device.VirtualDevice.ConnectInfo()
 830         nic.device.connectable.startConnected = bool(device_infos.get('start_connected', True))
 831         nic.device.connectable.allowGuestControl = bool(device_infos.get('allow_guest_control', True))
 832         nic.device.connectable.connected = True

 834             nic.device.addressType = 'manual'
 835             nic.device.macAddress = device_infos['mac']
 836         else:
 837             nic.device.addressType = 'generated'
 838 
 839         return nic

 841     def integer_value(self, input_value, name):
 842         """
 843         Function to return int value for given input, else return error
 844         Args:
 845             input_value: Input value to retrieve int value from
 846             name:  Name of the Input value (used to build error message)
 847         Returns: (int) if integer value can be obtained, otherwise will send a error message.

 854             self.module.fail_json(msg='"%s" attribute should be an'
 855                                   ' integer value.' % name)

 858 class PyVmomiCache(object):
 859     """ This class caches references to objects which are requested multiples times but not modified """
 860 
 861     def __init__(self, content, dc_name=None):
 862         self.content = content
 863         self.dc_name = dc_name
 864         self.networks = {}
 865         self.clusters = {}
 866         self.esx_hosts = {}
 867         self.parent_datacenters = {}
 868 
 869     def find_obj(self, content, types, name, confine_to_datacenter=True):
 870         """ Wrapper around find_obj to set datacenter context """
 871         result = find_obj(content, types, name)
 872         if result and confine_to_datacenter:
 873             if to_text(self.get_parent_datacenter(result).name) != to_text(self.dc_name):
 874                 result = None
 875                 objects = self.get_all_objs(content, types, confine_to_datacenter=True)
 876                 for obj in objects:
 877                     if name is None or to_text(obj.name) == to_text(name):
 878                         return obj
 879         return result
 880 
 881     def get_all_objs(self, content, types, confine_to_datacenter=True):
 882         """ Wrapper around get_all_objs to set datacenter context """
 883         objects = get_all_objs(content, types)
 884         if confine_to_datacenter:
 885             if hasattr(objects, 'items'):
 886                 # resource pools come back as a dictionary
 887                 # make a copy
 888                 for k, v in tuple(objects.items()):
 889                     parent_dc = self.get_parent_datacenter(k)
 890                     if parent_dc.name != self.dc_name:
 891                         del objects[k]
 892             else:
 893                 # everything else should be a list
 894                 objects = [x for x in objects if self.get_parent_datacenter(x).name == self.dc_name]
 895 
 896         return objects
 897 
 898     def get_network(self, network):
 899         network = quote_obj_name(network)
 900 
 901         if network not in self.networks:
 902             self.networks[network] = self.find_obj(self.content, [vim.Network], network)
 903 
 904         return self.networks[network]
 905 
 906     def get_cluster(self, cluster):
 907         if cluster not in self.clusters:
 908             self.clusters[cluster] = self.find_obj(self.content, [vim.ClusterComputeResource], cluster)
 909 
 910         return self.clusters[cluster]
 911 
 912     def get_esx_host(self, host):
 913         if host not in self.esx_hosts:
 914             self.esx_hosts[host] = self.find_obj(self.content, [vim.HostSystem], host)
 915 
 916         return self.esx_hosts[host]
 917 
 918     def get_parent_datacenter(self, obj):
 919         """ Walk the parent tree to find the objects datacenter """
 920         if isinstance(obj, vim.Datacenter):
 921             return obj
 922         if obj in self.parent_datacenters:
 923             return self.parent_datacenters[obj]
 924         datacenter = None
 925         while True:
 926             if not hasattr(obj, 'parent'):
 927                 break
 928             obj = obj.parent
 929             if isinstance(obj, vim.Datacenter):
 930                 datacenter = obj
 931                 break
 932         self.parent_datacenters[obj] = datacenter
 933         return datacenter

 936 class PyVmomiHelper(PyVmomi):
 937     def __init__(self, module):
 938         super(PyVmomiHelper, self).__init__(module)
 939         self.device_helper = PyVmomiDeviceHelper(self.module)
 940         self.configspec = None
 941         self.relospec = None
 942         self.change_detected = False  # a change was detected and needs to be applied through reconfiguration
 943         self.change_applied = False   # a change was applied meaning at least one task succeeded
 944         self.customspec = None
 945         self.cache = PyVmomiCache(self.content, dc_name=self.params['datacenter'])
 946 
 947     def gather_facts(self, vm):
 948         return gather_vm_facts(self.content, vm)
 949 
 950     def remove_vm(self, vm, delete_from_inventory=False):
 951         # https://www.vmware.com/support/developer/converter-sdk/conv60_apireference/vim.ManagedEntity.html#destroy
 952         if vm.summary.runtime.powerState.lower() == 'poweredon':
 953             self.module.fail_json(msg="Virtual machine %s found in 'powered on' state, "
 954                                       "please use 'force' parameter to remove or poweroff VM "
 955                                       "and try removing VM again." % vm.name)
 956         # Delete VM from Inventory
 957         if delete_from_inventory:
 958             try:
 959                 vm.UnregisterVM()
 960             except (vim.fault.TaskInProgress,
 961                     vmodl.RuntimeFault) as e:
 962                 return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': e.msg, 'op': 'UnregisterVM'}
 963             self.change_applied = True
 964             return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': False}
 965         # Delete VM from Disk
 966         task = vm.Destroy()
 967         self.wait_for_task(task)
 968         if task.info.state == 'error':
 969             return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'destroy'}
 970         else:
 971             return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': False}
 972 
 973     def configure_guestid(self, vm_obj, vm_creation=False):
 974         # guest_id is not required when using templates
 975         if self.params['template']:
 976             return
 977 
 978         # guest_id is only mandatory on VM creation
 979         if vm_creation and self.params['guest_id'] is None:
 980             self.module.fail_json(msg="guest_id attribute is mandatory for VM creation")
 981 
 982         if self.params['guest_id'] and \
 983                 (vm_obj is None or self.params['guest_id'].lower() != vm_obj.summary.config.guestId.lower()):
 984             self.change_detected = True
 985             self.configspec.guestId = self.params['guest_id']

1015                     self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.mem_reservation or hardware.memory_reservation should be an integer value.")
1016

1020                     rai_change_detected = True

1048     def configure_cpu_and_memory(self, vm_obj, vm_creation=False):
1049         # set cpu/memory/etc
1050         if 'hardware' in self.params:
1051             if 'num_cpus' in self.params['hardware']:
1052                 try:
1053                     num_cpus = int(self.params['hardware']['num_cpus'])
1054                 except ValueError:
1055                     self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.num_cpus attribute should be an integer value.")
1056                 # check VM power state and cpu hot-add/hot-remove state before re-config VM
1057                 if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn:
1058                     if not vm_obj.config.cpuHotRemoveEnabled and num_cpus < vm_obj.config.hardware.numCPU:
1059                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Configured cpu number is less than the cpu number of the VM, "
1060                                                   "cpuHotRemove is not enabled")
1061                     if not vm_obj.config.cpuHotAddEnabled and num_cpus > vm_obj.config.hardware.numCPU:
1062                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Configured cpu number is more than the cpu number of the VM, "
1063                                                   "cpuHotAdd is not enabled")
1064 
1065                 if 'num_cpu_cores_per_socket' in self.params['hardware']:
1066                     try:
1067                         num_cpu_cores_per_socket = int(self.params['hardware']['num_cpu_cores_per_socket'])
1068                     except ValueError:
1069                         self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.num_cpu_cores_per_socket attribute "
1070                                                   "should be an integer value.")
1071                     if num_cpus % num_cpu_cores_per_socket != 0:
1072                         self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.num_cpus attribute should be a multiple "
1073                                                   "of hardware.num_cpu_cores_per_socket")
1074                     self.configspec.numCoresPerSocket = num_cpu_cores_per_socket
1075                     if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.numCoresPerSocket != vm_obj.config.hardware.numCoresPerSocket:
1076                         self.change_detected = True
1077                 self.configspec.numCPUs = num_cpus
1078                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.numCPUs != vm_obj.config.hardware.numCPU:
1079                     self.change_detected = True
1080             # num_cpu is mandatory for VM creation
1081             elif vm_creation and not self.params['template']:
1082                 self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.num_cpus attribute is mandatory for VM creation")
1083 
1084             if 'memory_mb' in self.params['hardware']:
1085                 try:
1086                     memory_mb = int(self.params['hardware']['memory_mb'])
1087                 except ValueError:
1088                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to parse hardware.memory_mb value."
1089                                               " Please refer the documentation and provide"
1090                                               " correct value.")
1091                 # check VM power state and memory hotadd state before re-config VM
1092                 if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn:
1093                     if vm_obj.config.memoryHotAddEnabled and memory_mb < vm_obj.config.hardware.memoryMB:
1094                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Configured memory is less than memory size of the VM, "
1095                                                   "operation is not supported")
1096                     elif not vm_obj.config.memoryHotAddEnabled and memory_mb != vm_obj.config.hardware.memoryMB:
1097                         self.module.fail_json(msg="memoryHotAdd is not enabled")
1098                 self.configspec.memoryMB = memory_mb
1099                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.memoryMB != vm_obj.config.hardware.memoryMB:
1100                     self.change_detected = True
1101             # memory_mb is mandatory for VM creation
1102             elif vm_creation and not self.params['template']:
1103                 self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.memory_mb attribute is mandatory for VM creation")
1104 
1105             if 'hotadd_memory' in self.params['hardware']:
1106                 if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn and \
1107                         vm_obj.config.memoryHotAddEnabled != bool(self.params['hardware']['hotadd_memory']):
1108                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Configure hotadd memory operation is not supported when VM is power on")
1109                 self.configspec.memoryHotAddEnabled = bool(self.params['hardware']['hotadd_memory'])
1110                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.memoryHotAddEnabled != vm_obj.config.memoryHotAddEnabled:
1111                     self.change_detected = True
1112 
1113             if 'hotadd_cpu' in self.params['hardware']:
1114                 if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn and \
1115                         vm_obj.config.cpuHotAddEnabled != bool(self.params['hardware']['hotadd_cpu']):
1116                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Configure hotadd cpu operation is not supported when VM is power on")
1117                 self.configspec.cpuHotAddEnabled = bool(self.params['hardware']['hotadd_cpu'])
1118                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.cpuHotAddEnabled != vm_obj.config.cpuHotAddEnabled:
1119                     self.change_detected = True
1120 
1121             if 'hotremove_cpu' in self.params['hardware']:
1122                 if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn and \
1123                         vm_obj.config.cpuHotRemoveEnabled != bool(self.params['hardware']['hotremove_cpu']):
1124                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Configure hotremove cpu operation is not supported when VM is power on")
1125                 self.configspec.cpuHotRemoveEnabled = bool(self.params['hardware']['hotremove_cpu'])
1126                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.cpuHotRemoveEnabled != vm_obj.config.cpuHotRemoveEnabled:
1127                     self.change_detected = True
1128 
1129             if 'memory_reservation_lock' in self.params['hardware']:
1130                 self.configspec.memoryReservationLockedToMax = bool(self.params['hardware']['memory_reservation_lock'])
1131                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.memoryReservationLockedToMax != vm_obj.config.memoryReservationLockedToMax:
1132                     self.change_detected = True
1133 
1134             if 'boot_firmware' in self.params['hardware']:
1135                 # boot firmware re-config can cause boot issue
1136                 if vm_obj is not None:
1137                     return
1138                 boot_firmware = self.params['hardware']['boot_firmware'].lower()
1139                 if boot_firmware not in ('bios', 'efi'):
1140                     self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.boot_firmware value is invalid [%s]."
1141                                               " Need one of ['bios', 'efi']." % boot_firmware)
1142                 self.configspec.firmware = boot_firmware
1143                 self.change_detected = True

1145     def sanitize_cdrom_params(self):
1146         # cdroms {'ide': [{num: 0, cdrom: []}, {}], 'sata': [{num: 0, cdrom: []}, {}, ...]}
1147         cdroms = {'ide': [], 'sata': []}
1148         expected_cdrom_spec = self.params.get('cdrom')
1149         if expected_cdrom_spec:
1150             for cdrom_spec in expected_cdrom_spec:
1151                 cdrom_spec['controller_type'] = cdrom_spec.get('controller_type', 'ide').lower()
1152                 if cdrom_spec['controller_type'] not in ['ide', 'sata']:
1153                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Invalid cdrom.controller_type: %s, valid value is 'ide' or 'sata'."
1154                                               % cdrom_spec['controller_type'])
1155 
1156                 cdrom_spec['state'] = cdrom_spec.get('state', 'present').lower()
1157                 if cdrom_spec['state'] not in ['present', 'absent']:
1158                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Invalid cdrom.state: %s, valid value is 'present', 'absent'."
1159                                               % cdrom_spec['state'])
1160 
1161                 if cdrom_spec['state'] == 'present':
1162                     if 'type' in cdrom_spec and cdrom_spec.get('type') not in ['none', 'client', 'iso']:
1163                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Invalid cdrom.type: %s, valid value is 'none', 'client' or 'iso'."
1164                                                   % cdrom_spec.get('type'))
1165                     if cdrom_spec.get('type') == 'iso' and not cdrom_spec.get('iso_path'):
1166                         self.module.fail_json(msg="cdrom.iso_path is mandatory when cdrom.type is set to iso.")
1167 
1168                 if cdrom_spec['controller_type'] == 'ide' and \
1169                         (cdrom_spec.get('controller_number') not in [0, 1] or cdrom_spec.get('unit_number') not in [0, 1]):
1170                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Invalid cdrom.controller_number: %s or cdrom.unit_number: %s, valid"
1171                                               " values are 0 or 1 for IDE controller." % (cdrom_spec.get('controller_number'), cdrom_spec.get('unit_number')))
1172 
1173                 if cdrom_spec['controller_type'] == 'sata' and \
1174                         (cdrom_spec.get('controller_number') not in range(0, 4) or cdrom_spec.get('unit_number') not in range(0, 30)):
1175                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Invalid cdrom.controller_number: %s or cdrom.unit_number: %s,"
1176                                               " valid controller_number value is 0-3, valid unit_number is 0-29"
1177                                               " for SATA controller." % (cdrom_spec.get('controller_number'), cdrom_spec.get('unit_number')))
1178 
1179                 ctl_exist = False
1180                 for exist_spec in cdroms.get(cdrom_spec['controller_type']):
1181                     if exist_spec['num'] == cdrom_spec['controller_number']:
1182                         ctl_exist = True
1183                         exist_spec['cdrom'].append(cdrom_spec)
1184                         break
1185                 if not ctl_exist:
1186                     cdroms.get(cdrom_spec['controller_type']).append({'num': cdrom_spec['controller_number'], 'cdrom': [cdrom_spec]})
1187 
1188         return cdroms
1189 
1190     def configure_cdrom(self, vm_obj):
1191         # Configure the VM CD-ROM
1192         if self.params.get('cdrom'):
1193             if vm_obj and vm_obj.config.template:
1194                 # Changing CD-ROM settings on a template is not supported
1195                 return
1196 
1197             if isinstance(self.params.get('cdrom'), dict):
1198                 self.configure_cdrom_dict(vm_obj)
1199             elif isinstance(self.params.get('cdrom'), list):
1200                 self.configure_cdrom_list(vm_obj)
1201 
1202     def configure_cdrom_dict(self, vm_obj):
1203         if self.params["cdrom"].get('type') not in ['none', 'client', 'iso']:
1204             self.module.fail_json(msg="cdrom.type is mandatory. Options are 'none', 'client', and 'iso'.")
1205         if self.params["cdrom"]['type'] == 'iso' and not self.params["cdrom"].get('iso_path'):
1206             self.module.fail_json(msg="cdrom.iso_path is mandatory when cdrom.type is set to iso.")
1207 
1208         cdrom_spec = None
1209         cdrom_devices = self.get_vm_cdrom_devices(vm=vm_obj)
1210         iso_path = self.params["cdrom"].get("iso_path")
1211         if len(cdrom_devices) == 0:
1212             # Creating new CD-ROM
1213             ide_devices = self.get_vm_ide_devices(vm=vm_obj)
1214             if len(ide_devices) == 0:
1215                 # Creating new IDE device
1216                 ide_ctl = self.device_helper.create_ide_controller()
1217                 ide_device = ide_ctl.device
1218                 self.change_detected = True
1219                 self.configspec.deviceChange.append(ide_ctl)
1220             else:
1221                 ide_device = ide_devices[0]
1222                 if len(ide_device.device) > 3:
1223                     self.module.fail_json(msg="hardware.cdrom specified for a VM or template which already has 4"
1224                                               " IDE devices of which none are a cdrom")
1225 
1226             cdrom_spec = self.device_helper.create_cdrom(ide_device=ide_device, cdrom_type=self.params["cdrom"]["type"],
1227                                                          iso_path=iso_path)
1228             if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn:
1229                 cdrom_spec.device.connectable.connected = (self.params["cdrom"]["type"] != "none")
1230 
1231         elif not self.device_helper.is_equal_cdrom(vm_obj=vm_obj, cdrom_device=cdrom_devices[0],
1232                                                    cdrom_type=self.params["cdrom"]["type"], iso_path=iso_path):
1233             self.device_helper.update_cdrom_config(vm_obj, self.params["cdrom"], cdrom_devices[0], iso_path=iso_path)
1234             cdrom_spec = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()
1235             cdrom_spec.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.edit
1236             cdrom_spec.device = cdrom_devices[0]
1237 
1238         if cdrom_spec:
1239             self.change_detected = True
1240             self.configspec.deviceChange.append(cdrom_spec)
1241 
1242     def configure_cdrom_list(self, vm_obj):
1243         configured_cdroms = self.sanitize_cdrom_params()
1244         cdrom_devices = self.get_vm_cdrom_devices(vm=vm_obj)
1245         # configure IDE CD-ROMs
1246         if configured_cdroms['ide']:
1247             ide_devices = self.get_vm_ide_devices(vm=vm_obj)
1248             for expected_cdrom_spec in configured_cdroms['ide']:
1249                 ide_device = None
1250                 for device in ide_devices:
1251                     if device.busNumber == expected_cdrom_spec['num']:
1252                         ide_device = device
1253                         break
1254                 # if not find the matched ide controller or no existing ide controller
1255                 if not ide_device:
1256                     ide_ctl = self.device_helper.create_ide_controller(bus_number=expected_cdrom_spec['num'])
1257                     ide_device = ide_ctl.device
1258                     self.change_detected = True
1259                     self.configspec.deviceChange.append(ide_ctl)
1260 
1261                 for cdrom in expected_cdrom_spec['cdrom']:
1262                     cdrom_device = None
1263                     iso_path = cdrom.get('iso_path')
1264                     unit_number = cdrom.get('unit_number')
1265                     for target_cdrom in cdrom_devices:
1266                         if target_cdrom.controllerKey == ide_device.key and target_cdrom.unitNumber == unit_number:
1267                             cdrom_device = target_cdrom
1268                             break
1269                     # create new CD-ROM
1270                     if not cdrom_device and cdrom.get('state') != 'absent':
1271                         if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOn:
1272                             self.module.fail_json(msg='CD-ROM attach to IDE controller not support hot-add.')
1273                         if len(ide_device.device) == 2:
1274                             self.module.fail_json(msg='Maximum number of CD-ROMs attached to IDE controller is 2.')
1275                         cdrom_spec = self.device_helper.create_cdrom(ide_device=ide_device, cdrom_type=cdrom['type'],
1276                                                                      iso_path=iso_path, unit_number=unit_number)
1277                         self.change_detected = True
1278                         self.configspec.deviceChange.append(cdrom_spec)
1279                     # re-configure CD-ROM
1280                     elif cdrom_device and cdrom.get('state') != 'absent' and \
1281                             not self.device_helper.is_equal_cdrom(vm_obj=vm_obj, cdrom_device=cdrom_device,
1282                                                                   cdrom_type=cdrom['type'], iso_path=iso_path):
1283                         self.device_helper.update_cdrom_config(vm_obj, cdrom, cdrom_device, iso_path=iso_path)
1284                         cdrom_spec = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()
1285                         cdrom_spec.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.edit
1286                         cdrom_spec.device = cdrom_device
1287                         self.change_detected = True
1288                         self.configspec.deviceChange.append(cdrom_spec)
1289                     # delete CD-ROM
1290                     elif cdrom_device and cdrom.get('state') == 'absent':
1291                         if vm_obj and vm_obj.runtime.powerState != vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOff:
1292                             self.module.fail_json(msg='CD-ROM attach to IDE controller not support hot-remove.')
1293                         cdrom_spec = self.device_helper.remove_cdrom(cdrom_device)
1294                         self.change_detected = True
1295                         self.configspec.deviceChange.append(cdrom_spec)
1296         # configure SATA CD-ROMs is not supported yet
1297         if configured_cdroms['sata']:
1298             pass
1299 
1300     def configure_hardware_params(self, vm_obj):
1301         """
1302         Function to configure hardware related configuration of virtual machine
1303         Args:
1304             vm_obj: virtual machine object
1305         """
1306         if 'hardware' in self.params:
1307             if 'max_connections' in self.params['hardware']:
1308                 # maxMksConnections == max_connections
1309                 self.configspec.maxMksConnections = int(self.params['hardware']['max_connections'])
1310                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.maxMksConnections != vm_obj.config.maxMksConnections:
1311                     self.change_detected = True
1312 
1313             if 'nested_virt' in self.params['hardware']:
1314                 self.configspec.nestedHVEnabled = bool(self.params['hardware']['nested_virt'])
1315                 if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.nestedHVEnabled != bool(vm_obj.config.nestedHVEnabled):
1316                     self.change_detected = True
1317 
1318             if 'version' in self.params['hardware']:
1319                 hw_version_check_failed = False
1320                 temp_version = self.params['hardware'].get('version', 10)
1321                 if isinstance(temp_version, str) and temp_version.lower() == 'latest':
1322                     # Check is to make sure vm_obj is not of type template
1323                     if vm_obj and not vm_obj.config.template:
1324                         try:
1325                             task = vm_obj.UpgradeVM_Task()
1326                             self.wait_for_task(task)
1327                             if task.info.state == 'error':
1328                                 return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'upgrade'}
1329                         except vim.fault.AlreadyUpgraded:
1330                             # Don't fail if VM is already upgraded.
1331                             pass
1332                 else:
1333                     try:
1334                         temp_version = int(temp_version)
1335                     except ValueError:
1336                         hw_version_check_failed = True
1337 
1338                     if temp_version not in range(3, 16):
1339                         hw_version_check_failed = True
1340 
1341                     if hw_version_check_failed:
1342                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to set hardware.version '%s' value as valid"
1343                                               " values range from 3 (ESX 2.x) to 14 (ESXi 6.5 and greater)." % temp_version)
1344                     # Hardware version is denoted as "vmx-10"
1345                     version = "vmx-%02d" % temp_version
1346                     self.configspec.version = version
1347                     if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.version != vm_obj.config.version:
1348                         self.change_detected = True
1349                     # Check is to make sure vm_obj is not of type template
1350                     if vm_obj and not vm_obj.config.template:
1351                         # VM exists and we need to update the hardware version
1352                         current_version = vm_obj.config.version
1353                         # current_version = "vmx-10"
1354                         version_digit = int(current_version.split("-", 1)[-1])
1355                         if temp_version < version_digit:
1356                             self.module.fail_json(msg="Current hardware version '%d' which is greater than the specified"
1357                                                   " version '%d'. Downgrading hardware version is"
1358                                                   " not supported. Please specify version greater"
1359                                                   " than the current version." % (version_digit,
1360                                                                                   temp_version))
1361                         new_version = "vmx-%02d" % temp_version
1362                         try:
1363                             task = vm_obj.UpgradeVM_Task(new_version)
1364                             self.wait_for_task(task)
1365                             if task.info.state == 'error':
1366                                 return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'upgrade'}
1367                         except vim.fault.AlreadyUpgraded:
1368                             # Don't fail if VM is already upgraded.
1369                             pass
1370 
1371             if 'virt_based_security' in self.params['hardware']:
1372                 host_version = self.select_host().summary.config.product.version
1373                 if int(host_version.split('.')[0]) < 6 or (int(host_version.split('.')[0]) == 6 and int(host_version.split('.')[1]) < 7):
1374                     self.module.fail_json(msg="ESXi version %s not support VBS." % host_version)
1375                 guest_ids = ['windows9_64Guest', 'windows9Server64Guest']
1376                 if vm_obj is None:
1377                     guestid = self.configspec.guestId
1378                 else:
1379                     guestid = vm_obj.summary.config.guestId
1380                 if guestid not in guest_ids:
1381                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Guest '%s' not support VBS." % guestid)
1382                 if (vm_obj is None and int(self.configspec.version.split('-')[1]) >= 14) or \
1383                         (vm_obj and int(vm_obj.config.version.split('-')[1]) >= 14 and (vm_obj.runtime.powerState == vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOff)):
1384                     self.configspec.flags = vim.vm.FlagInfo()
1385                     self.configspec.flags.vbsEnabled = bool(self.params['hardware']['virt_based_security'])
1386                     if bool(self.params['hardware']['virt_based_security']):
1387                         self.configspec.flags.vvtdEnabled = True
1388                         self.configspec.nestedHVEnabled = True
1389                         if (vm_obj is None and self.configspec.firmware == 'efi') or \
1390                                 (vm_obj and vm_obj.config.firmware == 'efi'):
1391                             self.configspec.bootOptions = vim.vm.BootOptions()
1392                             self.configspec.bootOptions.efiSecureBootEnabled = True
1393                         else:
1394                             self.module.fail_json(msg="Not support VBS when firmware is BIOS.")
1395                     if vm_obj is None or self.configspec.flags.vbsEnabled != vm_obj.config.flags.vbsEnabled:
1396                         self.change_detected = True
1397 
1398     def get_device_by_type(self, vm=None, type=None):
1399         device_list = []
1400         if vm is None or type is None:
1401             return device_list
1402         for device in vm.config.hardware.device:
1403             if isinstance(device, type):
1404                 device_list.append(device)
1405 
1406         return device_list

1411     def get_vm_ide_devices(self, vm=None):

1414     def get_vm_network_interfaces(self, vm=None):

1428     def sanitize_network_params(self):
1429         """
1430         Sanitize user provided network provided params
1431 
1432         Returns: A sanitized list of network params, else fails
1433 
1434         """
1435         network_devices = list()
1436         # Clean up user data here
1437         for network in self.params['networks']:
1438             if 'name' not in network and 'vlan' not in network:
1439                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Please specify at least a network name or"
1440                                           " a VLAN name under VM network list.")
1441 
1442             if 'name' in network and self.cache.get_network(network['name']) is None:
1443                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Network '%(name)s' does not exist." % network)
1444             elif 'vlan' in network:
1445                 dvps = self.cache.get_all_objs(self.content, [vim.dvs.DistributedVirtualPortgroup])
1446                 for dvp in dvps:
1447                     if hasattr(dvp.config.defaultPortConfig, 'vlan') and \
1448                             isinstance(dvp.config.defaultPortConfig.vlan.vlanId, int) and \
1449                             str(dvp.config.defaultPortConfig.vlan.vlanId) == str(network['vlan']):
1450                         network['name'] = dvp.config.name
1451                         break
1452                     if 'dvswitch_name' in network and \
1453                             dvp.config.distributedVirtualSwitch.name == network['dvswitch_name'] and \
1454                             dvp.config.name == network['vlan']:
1455                         network['name'] = dvp.config.name
1456                         break
1457 
1458                     if dvp.config.name == network['vlan']:
1459                         network['name'] = dvp.config.name
1460                         break
1461                 else:
1462                     self.module.fail_json(msg="VLAN '%(vlan)s' does not exist." % network)
1463 
1464             if 'type' in network:
1465                 if network['type'] not in ['dhcp', 'static']:
1466                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Network type '%(type)s' is not a valid parameter."
1467                                               " Valid parameters are ['dhcp', 'static']." % network)
1468                 if network['type'] != 'static' and ('ip' in network or 'netmask' in network):
1469                     self.module.fail_json(msg='Static IP information provided for network "%(name)s",'
1470                                               ' but "type" is set to "%(type)s".' % network)
1471             else:
1472                 # Type is optional parameter, if user provided IP or Subnet assume
1473                 # network type as 'static'
1474                 if 'ip' in network or 'netmask' in network:
1475                     network['type'] = 'static'
1476                 else:
1477                     # User wants network type as 'dhcp'
1478                     network['type'] = 'dhcp'
1479 
1480             if network.get('type') == 'static':
1481                 if 'ip' in network and 'netmask' not in network:
1482                     self.module.fail_json(msg="'netmask' is required if 'ip' is"
1483                                               " specified under VM network list.")
1484                 if 'ip' not in network and 'netmask' in network:
1485                     self.module.fail_json(msg="'ip' is required if 'netmask' is"
1486                                               " specified under VM network list.")
1487 
1488             validate_device_types = ['pcnet32', 'vmxnet2', 'vmxnet3', 'e1000', 'e1000e', 'sriov']
1489             if 'device_type' in network and network['device_type'] not in validate_device_types:
1490                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Device type specified '%s' is not valid."
1491                                           " Please specify correct device"
1492                                           " type from ['%s']." % (network['device_type'],
1493                                                                   "', '".join(validate_device_types)))
1494 
1495             if 'mac' in network and not is_mac(network['mac']):
1496                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Device MAC address '%s' is invalid."
1497                                           " Please provide correct MAC address." % network['mac'])
1498 
1499             network_devices.append(network)
1500 
1501         return network_devices

1503     def configure_network(self, vm_obj):
1504         # Ignore empty networks, this permits to keep networks when deploying a template/cloning a VM
1505         if len(self.params['networks']) == 0:
1506             return
1507 
1508         network_devices = self.sanitize_network_params()
1509 
1510         # List current device for Clone or Idempotency
1511         current_net_devices = self.get_vm_network_interfaces(vm=vm_obj)
1512         if len(network_devices) < len(current_net_devices):
1513             self.module.fail_json(msg="Given network device list is lesser than current VM device list (%d < %d). "
1514                                       "Removing interfaces is not allowed"
1515                                       % (len(network_devices), len(current_net_devices)))
1516 
1517         for key in range(0, len(network_devices)):
1518             nic_change_detected = False
1519             network_name = network_devices[key]['name']
1520             if key < len(current_net_devices) and (vm_obj or self.params['template']):
1521                 # We are editing existing network devices, this is either when
1522                 # are cloning from VM or Template
1523                 nic = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()
1524                 nic.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.edit
1525 
1526                 nic.device = current_net_devices[key]
1527                 if ('wake_on_lan' in network_devices[key] and
1528                         nic.device.wakeOnLanEnabled != network_devices[key].get('wake_on_lan')):
1529                     nic.device.wakeOnLanEnabled = network_devices[key].get('wake_on_lan')
1530                     nic_change_detected = True
1531                 if ('start_connected' in network_devices[key] and
1532                         nic.device.connectable.startConnected != network_devices[key].get('start_connected')):
1533                     nic.device.connectable.startConnected = network_devices[key].get('start_connected')
1534                     nic_change_detected = True
1535                 if ('allow_guest_control' in network_devices[key] and
1536                         nic.device.connectable.allowGuestControl != network_devices[key].get('allow_guest_control')):
1537                     nic.device.connectable.allowGuestControl = network_devices[key].get('allow_guest_control')
1538                     nic_change_detected = True
1539 
1540                 if nic.device.deviceInfo.summary != network_name:
1541                     nic.device.deviceInfo.summary = network_name
1542                     nic_change_detected = True
1543                 if 'device_type' in network_devices[key]:
1544                     device = self.device_helper.get_device(network_devices[key]['device_type'], network_name)
1545                     device_class = type(device)
1546                     if not isinstance(nic.device, device_class):
1547                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Changing the device type is not possible when interface is already present. "
1548                                                   "The failing device type is %s" % network_devices[key]['device_type'])
1549                 # Changing mac address has no effect when editing interface
1550                 if 'mac' in network_devices[key] and nic.device.macAddress != current_net_devices[key].macAddress:
1551                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Changing MAC address has not effect when interface is already present. "
1552                                               "The failing new MAC address is %s" % nic.device.macAddress)
1553 
1554             else:
1555                 # Default device type is vmxnet3, VMware best practice
1556                 device_type = network_devices[key].get('device_type', 'vmxnet3')
1557                 nic = self.device_helper.create_nic(device_type,
1558                                                     'Network Adapter %s' % (key + 1),
1559                                                     network_devices[key])
1560                 nic.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.add
1561                 nic_change_detected = True
1562 
1563             if hasattr(self.cache.get_network(network_name), 'portKeys'):
1564                 # VDS switch
1565 
1566                 pg_obj = None
1567                 if 'dvswitch_name' in network_devices[key]:
1568                     dvs_name = network_devices[key]['dvswitch_name']
1569                     dvs_obj = find_dvs_by_name(self.content, dvs_name)
1570                     if dvs_obj is None:
1571                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Unable to find distributed virtual switch %s" % dvs_name)
1572                     pg_obj = find_dvspg_by_name(dvs_obj, network_name)
1573                     if pg_obj is None:
1574                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Unable to find distributed port group %s" % network_name)
1575                 else:
1576                     pg_obj = self.cache.find_obj(self.content, [vim.dvs.DistributedVirtualPortgroup], network_name)
1577 
1578                 # TODO: (akasurde) There is no way to find association between resource pool and distributed virtual portgroup
1579                 # For now, check if we are able to find distributed virtual switch
1580                 if not pg_obj.config.distributedVirtualSwitch:
1581                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to find distributed virtual switch which is associated with"
1582                                               " distributed virtual portgroup '%s'. Make sure hostsystem is associated with"
1583                                               " the given distributed virtual portgroup. Also, check if user has correct"
1584                                               " permission to access distributed virtual switch in the given portgroup." % pg_obj.name)
1585                 if (nic.device.backing and
1586                     (not hasattr(nic.device.backing, 'port') or
1587                      (nic.device.backing.port.portgroupKey != pg_obj.key or
1588                       nic.device.backing.port.switchUuid != pg_obj.config.distributedVirtualSwitch.uuid))):
1589                     nic_change_detected = True
1590 
1591                 dvs_port_connection = vim.dvs.PortConnection()
1592                 dvs_port_connection.portgroupKey = pg_obj.key
1593                 # If user specifies distributed port group without associating to the hostsystem on which
1594                 # virtual machine is going to be deployed then we get error. We can infer that there is no
1595                 # association between given distributed port group and host system.
1596                 host_system = self.params.get('esxi_hostname')
1597                 if host_system and host_system not in [host.config.host.name for host in pg_obj.config.distributedVirtualSwitch.config.host]:
1598                     self.module.fail_json(msg="It seems that host system '%s' is not associated with distributed"
1599                                               " virtual portgroup '%s'. Please make sure host system is associated"
1600                                               " with given distributed virtual portgroup" % (host_system, pg_obj.name))
1601                 dvs_port_connection.switchUuid = pg_obj.config.distributedVirtualSwitch.uuid
1602                 nic.device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualEthernetCard.DistributedVirtualPortBackingInfo()
1603                 nic.device.backing.port = dvs_port_connection
1604 
1605             elif isinstance(self.cache.get_network(network_name), vim.OpaqueNetwork):
1606                 # NSX-T Logical Switch
1607                 nic.device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualEthernetCard.OpaqueNetworkBackingInfo()
1608                 network_id = self.cache.get_network(network_name).summary.opaqueNetworkId
1609                 nic.device.backing.opaqueNetworkType = 'nsx.LogicalSwitch'
1610                 nic.device.backing.opaqueNetworkId = network_id
1611                 nic.device.deviceInfo.summary = 'nsx.LogicalSwitch: %s' % network_id
1612                 nic_change_detected = True
1613             else:
1614                 # vSwitch
1615                 if not isinstance(nic.device.backing, vim.vm.device.VirtualEthernetCard.NetworkBackingInfo):
1616                     nic.device.backing = vim.vm.device.VirtualEthernetCard.NetworkBackingInfo()
1617                     nic_change_detected = True
1618 
1619                 net_obj = self.cache.get_network(network_name)
1620                 if nic.device.backing.network != net_obj:
1621                     nic.device.backing.network = net_obj
1622                     nic_change_detected = True
1623 
1624                 if nic.device.backing.deviceName != network_name:
1625                     nic.device.backing.deviceName = network_name
1626                     nic_change_detected = True
1627 
1628             if nic_change_detected:
1629                 # Change to fix the issue found while configuring opaque network
1630                 # VMs cloned from a template with opaque network will get disconnected
1631                 # Replacing deprecated config parameter with relocation Spec
1632                 if isinstance(self.cache.get_network(network_name), vim.OpaqueNetwork):
1633                     self.relospec.deviceChange.append(nic)
1634                 else:
1635                     self.configspec.deviceChange.append(nic)
1636                 self.change_detected = True
1637 
1638     def configure_vapp_properties(self, vm_obj):
1639         if len(self.params['vapp_properties']) == 0:
1640             return
1641 
1642         for x in self.params['vapp_properties']:
1643             if not x.get('id'):
1644                 self.module.fail_json(msg="id is required to set vApp property")
1645 
1646         new_vmconfig_spec = vim.vApp.VmConfigSpec()
1647 
1648         if vm_obj:
1649             # VM exists
1650             # This is primarily for vcsim/integration tests, unset vAppConfig was not seen on my deployments
1651             orig_spec = vm_obj.config.vAppConfig if vm_obj.config.vAppConfig else new_vmconfig_spec
1652 
1653             vapp_properties_current = dict((x.id, x) for x in orig_spec.property)
1654             vapp_properties_to_change = dict((x['id'], x) for x in self.params['vapp_properties'])
1655 
1656             # each property must have a unique key
1657             # init key counter with max value + 1
1658             all_keys = [x.key for x in orig_spec.property]
1659             new_property_index = max(all_keys) + 1 if all_keys else 0
1660 
1661             for property_id, property_spec in vapp_properties_to_change.items():
1662                 is_property_changed = False
1663                 new_vapp_property_spec = vim.vApp.PropertySpec()
1664 
1665                 if property_id in vapp_properties_current:
1666                     if property_spec.get('operation') == 'remove':
1667                         new_vapp_property_spec.operation = 'remove'
1668                         new_vapp_property_spec.removeKey = vapp_properties_current[property_id].key
1669                         is_property_changed = True
1670                     else:
1671                         # this is 'edit' branch
1672                         new_vapp_property_spec.operation = 'edit'
1673                         new_vapp_property_spec.info = vapp_properties_current[property_id]
1674                         try:
1675                             for property_name, property_value in property_spec.items():
1676 
1677                                 if property_name == 'operation':
1678                                     # operation is not an info object property
1679                                     # if set to anything other than 'remove' we don't fail
1680                                     continue
1681 
1682                                 # Updating attributes only if needed
1683                                 if getattr(new_vapp_property_spec.info, property_name) != property_value:
1684                                     setattr(new_vapp_property_spec.info, property_name, property_value)
1685                                     is_property_changed = True
1686 
1687                         except Exception as e:
1688                             msg = "Failed to set vApp property field='%s' and value='%s'. Error: %s" % (property_name, property_value, to_text(e))
1689                             self.module.fail_json(msg=msg)
1690                 else:
1691                     if property_spec.get('operation') == 'remove':
1692                         # attempt to delete non-existent property
1693                         continue
1694 
1695                     # this is add new property branch
1696                     new_vapp_property_spec.operation = 'add'
1697 
1698                     property_info = vim.vApp.PropertyInfo()
1699                     property_info.classId = property_spec.get('classId')
1700                     property_info.instanceId = property_spec.get('instanceId')
1701                     property_info.id = property_spec.get('id')
1702                     property_info.category = property_spec.get('category')
1703                     property_info.label = property_spec.get('label')
1704                     property_info.type = property_spec.get('type', 'string')
1705                     property_info.userConfigurable = property_spec.get('userConfigurable', True)
1706                     property_info.defaultValue = property_spec.get('defaultValue')
1707                     property_info.value = property_spec.get('value', '')
1708                     property_info.description = property_spec.get('description')
1709 
1710                     new_vapp_property_spec.info = property_info
1711                     new_vapp_property_spec.info.key = new_property_index
1712                     new_property_index += 1
1713                     is_property_changed = True
1714 
1715                 if is_property_changed:
1716                     new_vmconfig_spec.property.append(new_vapp_property_spec)
1717         else:
1718             # New VM
1719             all_keys = [x.key for x in new_vmconfig_spec.property]
1720             new_property_index = max(all_keys) + 1 if all_keys else 0
1721             vapp_properties_to_change = dict((x['id'], x) for x in self.params['vapp_properties'])
1722             is_property_changed = False
1723 
1724             for property_id, property_spec in vapp_properties_to_change.items():
1725                 new_vapp_property_spec = vim.vApp.PropertySpec()
1726                 # this is add new property branch
1727                 new_vapp_property_spec.operation = 'add'
1728 
1729                 property_info = vim.vApp.PropertyInfo()
1730                 property_info.classId = property_spec.get('classId')
1731                 property_info.instanceId = property_spec.get('instanceId')
1732                 property_info.id = property_spec.get('id')
1733                 property_info.category = property_spec.get('category')
1734                 property_info.label = property_spec.get('label')
1735                 property_info.type = property_spec.get('type', 'string')
1736                 property_info.userConfigurable = property_spec.get('userConfigurable', True)
1737                 property_info.defaultValue = property_spec.get('defaultValue')
1738                 property_info.value = property_spec.get('value', '')
1739                 property_info.description = property_spec.get('description')
1740 
1741                 new_vapp_property_spec.info = property_info
1742                 new_vapp_property_spec.info.key = new_property_index
1743                 new_property_index += 1
1744                 is_property_changed = True
1745 
1746                 if is_property_changed:
1747                     new_vmconfig_spec.property.append(new_vapp_property_spec)
1748 
1749         if new_vmconfig_spec.property:
1750             self.configspec.vAppConfig = new_vmconfig_spec
1751             self.change_detected = True
1752 
1753     def customize_customvalues(self, vm_obj, config_spec):
1754         if len(self.params['customvalues']) == 0:
1755             return
1756 
1757         vm_custom_spec = config_spec
1758         vm_custom_spec.extraConfig = []
1759 
1760         changed = False
1761         facts = self.gather_facts(vm_obj)
1762         for kv in self.params['customvalues']:
1763             if 'key' not in kv or 'value' not in kv:
1764                 self.module.exit_json(msg="customvalues items required both 'key' and 'value' fields.")
1765 
1766             # If kv is not kv fetched from facts, change it
1767             if kv['key'] not in facts['customvalues'] or facts['customvalues'][kv['key']] != kv['value']:
1768                 option = vim.option.OptionValue()
1769                 option.key = kv['key']
1770                 option.value = kv['value']
1771 
1772                 vm_custom_spec.extraConfig.append(option)
1773                 changed = True
1774 
1775             if changed:
1776                 self.change_detected = True

1778     def customize_vm(self, vm_obj):
1779 
1780         # User specified customization specification
1781         custom_spec_name = self.params.get('customization_spec')
1782         if custom_spec_name:
1783             cc_mgr = self.content.customizationSpecManager
1784             if cc_mgr.DoesCustomizationSpecExist(name=custom_spec_name):
1785                 temp_spec = cc_mgr.GetCustomizationSpec(name=custom_spec_name)
1786                 self.customspec = temp_spec.spec
1787                 return
1788             else:
1789                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Unable to find customization specification"
1790                                           " '%s' in given configuration." % custom_spec_name)
1791 
1792         # Network settings
1793         adaptermaps = []
1794         for network in self.params['networks']:
1795 
1796             guest_map = vim.vm.customization.AdapterMapping()
1797             guest_map.adapter = vim.vm.customization.IPSettings()
1798 
1799             if 'ip' in network and 'netmask' in network:
1800                 guest_map.adapter.ip = vim.vm.customization.FixedIp()
1801                 guest_map.adapter.ip.ipAddress = str(network['ip'])
1802                 guest_map.adapter.subnetMask = str(network['netmask'])
1803             elif 'type' in network and network['type'] == 'dhcp':
1804                 guest_map.adapter.ip = vim.vm.customization.DhcpIpGenerator()
1805 
1806             if 'gateway' in network:
1807                 guest_map.adapter.gateway = network['gateway']
1808 
1809             # On Windows, DNS domain and DNS servers can be set by network interface
1810             # https://pubs.vmware.com/vi3/sdk/ReferenceGuide/vim.vm.customization.IPSettings.html
1811             if 'domain' in network:
1812                 guest_map.adapter.dnsDomain = network['domain']
1813             elif 'domain' in self.params['customization']:
1814                 guest_map.adapter.dnsDomain = self.params['customization']['domain']
1815 
1816             if 'dns_servers' in network:
1817                 guest_map.adapter.dnsServerList = network['dns_servers']
1818             elif 'dns_servers' in self.params['customization']:
1819                 guest_map.adapter.dnsServerList = self.params['customization']['dns_servers']
1820 
1821             adaptermaps.append(guest_map)
1822 
1823         # Global DNS settings
1824         globalip = vim.vm.customization.GlobalIPSettings()
1825         if 'dns_servers' in self.params['customization']:
1826             globalip.dnsServerList = self.params['customization']['dns_servers']
1827 
1828         # TODO: Maybe list the different domains from the interfaces here by default ?
1829         if 'dns_suffix' in self.params['customization']:
1830             dns_suffix = self.params['customization']['dns_suffix']
1831             if isinstance(dns_suffix, list):
1832                 globalip.dnsSuffixList = " ".join(dns_suffix)
1833             else:
1834                 globalip.dnsSuffixList = dns_suffix
1835         elif 'domain' in self.params['customization']:
1836             globalip.dnsSuffixList = self.params['customization']['domain']
1837 
1838         if self.params['guest_id']:
1839             guest_id = self.params['guest_id']
1840         else:
1841             guest_id = vm_obj.summary.config.guestId
1842 
1843         # For windows guest OS, use SysPrep
1844         # https://pubs.vmware.com/vi3/sdk/ReferenceGuide/vim.vm.customization.Sysprep.html#field_detail
1845         if 'win' in guest_id:
1846             ident = vim.vm.customization.Sysprep()
1847 
1848             ident.userData = vim.vm.customization.UserData()
1849 
1850             # Setting hostName, orgName and fullName is mandatory, so we set some default when missing
1851             ident.userData.computerName = vim.vm.customization.FixedName()
1852             # computer name will be truncated to 15 characters if using VM name
1853             default_name = self.params['name'].replace(' ', '')
1854             punctuation = string.punctuation.replace('-', '')
1855             default_name = ''.join([c for c in default_name if c not in punctuation])
1856             ident.userData.computerName.name = str(self.params['customization'].get('hostname', default_name[0:15]))
1857             ident.userData.fullName = str(self.params['customization'].get('fullname', 'Administrator'))
1858             ident.userData.orgName = str(self.params['customization'].get('orgname', 'ACME'))
1859 
1860             if 'productid' in self.params['customization']:
1861                 ident.userData.productId = str(self.params['customization']['productid'])
1862 
1863             ident.guiUnattended = vim.vm.customization.GuiUnattended()
1864 
1865             if 'autologon' in self.params['customization']:
1866                 ident.guiUnattended.autoLogon = self.params['customization']['autologon']
1867                 ident.guiUnattended.autoLogonCount = self.params['customization'].get('autologoncount', 1)
1868 
1869             if 'timezone' in self.params['customization']:
1870                 # Check if timezone value is a int before proceeding.
1871                 ident.guiUnattended.timeZone = self.device_helper.integer_value(
1872                     self.params['customization']['timezone'],
1873                     'customization.timezone')
1874 
1875             ident.identification = vim.vm.customization.Identification()
1876 
1877             if self.params['customization'].get('password', '') != '':
1878                 ident.guiUnattended.password = vim.vm.customization.Password()
1879                 ident.guiUnattended.password.value = str(self.params['customization']['password'])
1880                 ident.guiUnattended.password.plainText = True
1881 
1882             if 'joindomain' in self.params['customization']:
1883                 if 'domainadmin' not in self.params['customization'] or 'domainadminpassword' not in self.params['customization']:
1884                     self.module.fail_json(msg="'domainadmin' and 'domainadminpassword' entries are mandatory in 'customization' section to use "
1885                                               "joindomain feature")
1886 
1887                 ident.identification.domainAdmin = str(self.params['customization']['domainadmin'])
1888                 ident.identification.joinDomain = str(self.params['customization']['joindomain'])
1889                 ident.identification.domainAdminPassword = vim.vm.customization.Password()

1942     def get_configured_disk_size(self, expected_disk_spec):
1943         # what size is it?
1944         if [x for x in expected_disk_spec.keys() if x.startswith('size_') or x == 'size']:
1945             # size, size_tb, size_gb, size_mb, size_kb
1946             if 'size' in expected_disk_spec:
1947                 size_regex = re.compile(r'(\d+(?:\.\d+)?)([tgmkTGMK][bB])')
1948                 disk_size_m = size_regex.match(expected_disk_spec['size'])
1949                 try:
1950                     if disk_size_m:
1951                         expected = disk_size_m.group(1)
1952                         unit = disk_size_m.group(2)
1953                     else:
1954                         raise ValueError
1955 
1956                     if re.match(r'\d+\.\d+', expected):
1957                         # We found float value in string, let's typecast it
1958                         expected = float(expected)
1959                     else:
1960                         # We found int value in string, let's typecast it
1961                         expected = int(expected)
1962 
1963                     if not expected or not unit:
1964                         raise ValueError
1965 
1966                 except (TypeError, ValueError, NameError):
1967                     # Common failure
1968                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to parse disk size please review value"
1969                                               " provided using documentation.")
1970             else:
1971                 param = [x for x in expected_disk_spec.keys() if x.startswith('size_')][0]
1972                 unit = param.split('_')[-1].lower()
1973                 expected = [x[1] for x in expected_disk_spec.items() if x[0].startswith('size_')][0]
1974                 expected = int(expected)
1975 
1976             disk_units = dict(tb=3, gb=2, mb=1, kb=0)
1977             if unit in disk_units:
1978                 unit = unit.lower()
1979                 return expected * (1024 ** disk_units[unit])
1980             else:
1981                 self.module.fail_json(msg="%s is not a supported unit for disk size."
1982                                           " Supported units are ['%s']." % (unit,
1983                                                                             "', '".join(disk_units.keys())))
1984 
1985         # No size found but disk, fail
1986         self.module.fail_json(
1987             msg="No size, size_kb, size_mb, size_gb or size_tb attribute found into disk configuration")
1988 
1989     def add_existing_vmdk(self, vm_obj, expected_disk_spec, diskspec, scsi_ctl):
1990         """
1991         Adds vmdk file described by expected_disk_spec['filename'], retrieves the file
1992         information and adds the correct spec to self.configspec.deviceChange.
1993         """
1994         filename = expected_disk_spec['filename']
1995         # If this is a new disk, or the disk file names are different
1996         if (vm_obj and diskspec.device.backing.fileName != filename) or vm_obj is None:
1997             diskspec.device.backing.fileName = filename
1998             diskspec.device.key = -1
1999             self.change_detected = True
2000             self.configspec.deviceChange.append(diskspec)

2002     def configure_disks(self, vm_obj):
2003         # Ignore empty disk list, this permits to keep disks when deploying a template/cloning a VM
2004         if len(self.params['disk']) == 0:
2005             return
2006 
2007         scsi_ctl = self.get_vm_scsi_controller(vm_obj)
2008 
2009         # Create scsi controller only if we are deploying a new VM, not a template or reconfiguring
2010         if vm_obj is None or scsi_ctl is None:
2011             scsi_ctl = self.device_helper.create_scsi_controller(self.get_scsi_type())
2012             self.change_detected = True
2013             self.configspec.deviceChange.append(scsi_ctl)
2014 
2015         disks = [x for x in vm_obj.config.hardware.device if isinstance(x, vim.vm.device.VirtualDisk)] \
2016             if vm_obj is not None else None
2017 
2018         if disks is not None and self.params.get('disk') and len(self.params.get('disk')) < len(disks):
2019             self.module.fail_json(msg="Provided disks configuration has less disks than "
2020                                       "the target object (%d vs %d)" % (len(self.params.get('disk')), len(disks)))
2021 
2022         disk_index = 0
2023         for expected_disk_spec in self.params.get('disk'):
2024             disk_modified = False
2025             # If we are manipulating and existing objects which has disks and disk_index is in disks
2026             if vm_obj is not None and disks is not None and disk_index < len(disks):
2027                 diskspec = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec()
2028                 # set the operation to edit so that it knows to keep other settings
2029                 diskspec.operation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.Operation.edit
2030                 diskspec.device = disks[disk_index]
2031             else:
2032                 diskspec = self.device_helper.create_scsi_disk(scsi_ctl, disk_index)
2033                 disk_modified = True
2034 
2035             # increment index for next disk search
2036             disk_index += 1
2037             # index 7 is reserved to SCSI controller
2038             if disk_index == 7:
2039                 disk_index += 1
2040 
2041             if 'disk_mode' in expected_disk_spec:
2042                 disk_mode = expected_disk_spec.get('disk_mode', 'persistent').lower()
2043                 valid_disk_mode = ['persistent', 'independent_persistent', 'independent_nonpersistent']
2044                 if disk_mode not in valid_disk_mode:
2045                     self.module.fail_json(msg="disk_mode specified is not valid."
2046                                               " Should be one of ['%s']" % "', '".join(valid_disk_mode))
2047 
2048                 if (vm_obj and diskspec.device.backing.diskMode != disk_mode) or (vm_obj is None):
2049                     diskspec.device.backing.diskMode = disk_mode
2050                     disk_modified = True
2051             else:
2052                 diskspec.device.backing.diskMode = "persistent"
2053 
2054             # is it thin?
2055             if 'type' in expected_disk_spec:
2056                 disk_type = expected_disk_spec.get('type', '').lower()
2057                 if disk_type == 'thin':
2058                     diskspec.device.backing.thinProvisioned = True
2059                 elif disk_type == 'eagerzeroedthick':
2060                     diskspec.device.backing.eagerlyScrub = True
2061 
2062             if 'filename' in expected_disk_spec and expected_disk_spec['filename'] is not None:
2063                 self.add_existing_vmdk(vm_obj, expected_disk_spec, diskspec, scsi_ctl)
2064                 continue
2065             elif vm_obj is None or self.params['template']:
2066                 # We are creating new VM or from Template
2067                 # Only create virtual device if not backed by vmdk in original template
2068                 if diskspec.device.backing.fileName == '':
2069                     diskspec.fileOperation = vim.vm.device.VirtualDeviceSpec.FileOperation.create
2070 
2071             # which datastore?
2072             if expected_disk_spec.get('datastore'):
2073                 # TODO: This is already handled by the relocation spec,
2074                 # but it needs to eventually be handled for all the
2075                 # other disks defined
2076                 pass
2077 
2078             kb = self.get_configured_disk_size(expected_disk_spec)
2079             # VMware doesn't allow to reduce disk sizes
2080             if kb < diskspec.device.capacityInKB:
2081                 self.module.fail_json(
2082                     msg="Given disk size is smaller than found (%d < %d). Reducing disks is not allowed." %
2083                         (kb, diskspec.device.capacityInKB))
2084 
2085             if kb != diskspec.device.capacityInKB or disk_modified:
2086                 diskspec.device.capacityInKB = kb
2087                 self.configspec.deviceChange.append(diskspec)
2088 
2089                 self.change_detected = True

2117     def get_recommended_datastore(self, datastore_cluster_obj=None):
2118         """
2119         Function to return Storage DRS recommended datastore from datastore cluster
2120         Args:
2121             datastore_cluster_obj: datastore cluster managed object
2122 
2123         Returns: Name of recommended datastore from the given datastore cluster
2124 
2125         """
2126         if datastore_cluster_obj is None:
2127             return None
2128         # Check if Datastore Cluster provided by user is SDRS ready
2129         sdrs_status = datastore_cluster_obj.podStorageDrsEntry.storageDrsConfig.podConfig.enabled
2130         if sdrs_status:
2131             # We can get storage recommendation only if SDRS is enabled on given datastorage cluster
2132             pod_sel_spec = vim.storageDrs.PodSelectionSpec()
2133             pod_sel_spec.storagePod = datastore_cluster_obj
2134             storage_spec = vim.storageDrs.StoragePlacementSpec()

2140                 rec_action = rec.recommendations[0].action[0]
2141                 return rec_action.destination.name
2142             except Exception:

2144                 pass
