2147         for ds in datastore_cluster_obj.childEntity:
2148             if isinstance(ds, vim.Datastore) and ds.summary.freeSpace > datastore_freespace:
2149                 # If datastore field is provided, filter destination datastores
2150                 if not self.is_datastore_valid(datastore_obj=ds):
2151                     continue
2152 
2153                 datastore = ds
2154                 datastore_freespace = ds.summary.freeSpace

2236     def obj_has_parent(self, obj, parent):
2237         if obj is None and parent is None:
2238             raise AssertionError()
2239         current_parent = obj
2240 
2241         while True:
2242             if current_parent.name == parent.name:
2243                 return True
2244 
2245             # Check if we have reached till root folder
2246             moid = current_parent._moId
2247             if moid in ['group-d1', 'ha-folder-root']:
2248                 return False
2249 
2250             current_parent = current_parent.parent
2251             if current_parent is None:
2252                 return False

2265     def find_folder(self, searchpath):
2266         """ Walk inventory objects one position of the searchpath at a time """
2267 
2268         # split the searchpath so we can iterate through it
2269         paths = [x.replace('/', '') for x in searchpath.split('/')]
2270         paths_total = len(paths) - 1
2271         position = 0
2272 
2273         # recursive walk while looking for next element in searchpath
2274         root = self.content.rootFolder
2275         while root and position <= paths_total:
2276             change = False
2277             if hasattr(root, 'childEntity'):
2278                 for child in root.childEntity:
2279                     if child.name == paths[position]:
2280                         root = child
2281                         position += 1
2282                         change = True
2283                         break
2284             elif isinstance(root, vim.Datacenter):
2285                 if hasattr(root, 'vmFolder'):
2286                     if root.vmFolder.name == paths[position]:
2287                         root = root.vmFolder
2288                         position += 1
2289                         change = True
2290             else:
2291                 root = None
2292 
2293             if not change:
2294                 root = None
2295 
2296         return root

2333     def deploy_vm(self):
2334         # https://github.com/vmware/pyvmomi-community-samples/blob/master/samples/clone_vm.py
2335         # https://www.vmware.com/support/developer/vc-sdk/visdk25pubs/ReferenceGuide/vim.vm.CloneSpec.html
2336         # https://www.vmware.com/support/developer/vc-sdk/visdk25pubs/ReferenceGuide/vim.vm.ConfigSpec.html
2337         # https://www.vmware.com/support/developer/vc-sdk/visdk41pubs/ApiReference/vim.vm.RelocateSpec.html
2338 
2339         # FIXME:
2340         #   - static IPs
2341 
2342         self.folder = self.params.get('folder', None)
2343         if self.folder is None:
2344             self.module.fail_json(msg="Folder is required parameter while deploying new virtual machine")
2345 
2346         # Prepend / if it was missing from the folder path, also strip trailing slashes
2347         if not self.folder.startswith('/'):
2348             self.folder = '/%(folder)s' % self.params
2349         self.folder = self.folder.rstrip('/')
2350 
2351         datacenter = self.cache.find_obj(self.content, [vim.Datacenter], self.params['datacenter'])
2352         if datacenter is None:
2353             self.module.fail_json(msg='No datacenter named %(datacenter)s was found' % self.params)
2354 
2355         dcpath = compile_folder_path_for_object(datacenter)
2356 
2357         # Nested folder does not have trailing /
2358         if not dcpath.endswith('/'):
2359             dcpath += '/'
2360 
2361         # Check for full path first in case it was already supplied
2362         if (self.folder.startswith(dcpath + self.params['datacenter'] + '/vm') or
2363                 self.folder.startswith(dcpath + '/' + self.params['datacenter'] + '/vm')):
2364             fullpath = self.folder
2365         elif self.folder.startswith('/vm/') or self.folder == '/vm':
2366             fullpath = "%s%s%s" % (dcpath, self.params['datacenter'], self.folder)
2367         elif self.folder.startswith('/'):
2368             fullpath = "%s%s/vm%s" % (dcpath, self.params['datacenter'], self.folder)
2369         else:
2370             fullpath = "%s%s/vm/%s" % (dcpath, self.params['datacenter'], self.folder)
2371 
2372         f_obj = self.content.searchIndex.FindByInventoryPath(fullpath)
2373 
2374         # abort if no strategy was successful
2375         if f_obj is None:
2376             # Add some debugging values in failure.
2377             details = {
2378                 'datacenter': datacenter.name,
2379                 'datacenter_path': dcpath,
2380                 'folder': self.folder,
2381                 'full_search_path': fullpath,
2382             }
2383             self.module.fail_json(msg='No folder %s matched in the search path : %s' % (self.folder, fullpath),
2384                                   details=details)
2385 
2386         destfolder = f_obj
2387 
2388         if self.params['template']:
2389             vm_obj = self.get_vm_or_template(template_name=self.params['template'])
2390             if vm_obj is None:
2391                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Could not find a template named %(template)s" % self.params)
2392         else:
2393             vm_obj = None
2394 
2395         # always get a resource_pool
2396         resource_pool = self.get_resource_pool()
2397 
2398         # set the destination datastore for VM & disks
2399         if self.params['datastore']:
2400             # Give precedence to datastore value provided by user
2401             # User may want to deploy VM to specific datastore.
2402             datastore_name = self.params['datastore']
2403             # Check if user has provided datastore cluster first
2404             datastore_cluster = self.cache.find_obj(self.content, [vim.StoragePod], datastore_name)
2405             if datastore_cluster:
2406                 # If user specified datastore cluster so get recommended datastore
2407                 datastore_name = self.get_recommended_datastore(datastore_cluster_obj=datastore_cluster)
2408             # Check if get_recommended_datastore or user specified datastore exists or not
2409             datastore = self.cache.find_obj(self.content, [vim.Datastore], datastore_name)
2410         else:
2411             (datastore, datastore_name) = self.select_datastore(vm_obj)
2412 
2413         self.configspec = vim.vm.ConfigSpec()
2414         self.configspec.deviceChange = []
2415         # create the relocation spec
2416         self.relospec = vim.vm.RelocateSpec()
2417         self.relospec.deviceChange = []
2418         self.configure_guestid(vm_obj=vm_obj, vm_creation=True)
2419         self.configure_cpu_and_memory(vm_obj=vm_obj, vm_creation=True)
2420         self.configure_hardware_params(vm_obj=vm_obj)
2421         self.configure_resource_alloc_info(vm_obj=vm_obj)
2422         self.configure_vapp_properties(vm_obj=vm_obj)
2423         self.configure_disks(vm_obj=vm_obj)
2424         self.configure_network(vm_obj=vm_obj)
2425         self.configure_cdrom(vm_obj=vm_obj)
2426 
2427         # Find if we need network customizations (find keys in dictionary that requires customizations)
2428         network_changes = False
2429         for nw in self.params['networks']:
2430             for key in nw:
2431                 # We don't need customizations for these keys
2432                 if key == 'type' and nw['type'] == 'dhcp':
2433                     network_changes = True
2434                     break
2435                 if key not in ('device_type', 'mac', 'name', 'vlan', 'type', 'start_connected', 'dvswitch_name'):
2436                     network_changes = True
2437                     break
2438 
2439         if len(self.params['customization']) > 0 or network_changes or self.params.get('customization_spec') is not None:
2440             self.customize_vm(vm_obj=vm_obj)
2441 
2442         clonespec = None
2443         clone_method = None
2444         try:
2445             if self.params['template']:
2446                 # Only select specific host when ESXi hostname is provided
2447                 if self.params['esxi_hostname']:
2448                     self.relospec.host = self.select_host()
2449                 self.relospec.datastore = datastore
2450 
2451                 # Convert disk present in template if is set
2452                 if self.params['convert']:
2453                     for device in vm_obj.config.hardware.device:
2454                         if isinstance(device, vim.vm.device.VirtualDisk):
2455                             disk_locator = vim.vm.RelocateSpec.DiskLocator()
2456                             disk_locator.diskBackingInfo = vim.vm.device.VirtualDisk.FlatVer2BackingInfo()
2457                             if self.params['convert'] in ['thin']:
2458                                 disk_locator.diskBackingInfo.thinProvisioned = True
2459                             if self.params['convert'] in ['eagerzeroedthick']:
2460                                 disk_locator.diskBackingInfo.eagerlyScrub = True
2461                             if self.params['convert'] in ['thick']:
2462                                 disk_locator.diskBackingInfo.diskMode = "persistent"
2463                             disk_locator.diskId = device.key
2464                             disk_locator.datastore = datastore
2465                             self.relospec.disk.append(disk_locator)
2466 
2467                 # https://www.vmware.com/support/developer/vc-sdk/visdk41pubs/ApiReference/vim.vm.RelocateSpec.html
2468                 # > pool: For a clone operation from a template to a virtual machine, this argument is required.
2469                 self.relospec.pool = resource_pool
2470                 linked_clone = self.params.get('linked_clone')
2471                 snapshot_src = self.params.get('snapshot_src', None)
2472                 if linked_clone:
2473                     if snapshot_src is not None:
2474                         self.relospec.diskMoveType = vim.vm.RelocateSpec.DiskMoveOptions.createNewChildDiskBacking
2475                     else:
2476                         self.module.fail_json(msg="Parameter 'linked_src' and 'snapshot_src' are"
2477                                                   " required together for linked clone operation.")
2478 
2479                 clonespec = vim.vm.CloneSpec(template=self.params['is_template'], location=self.relospec)
2480                 if self.customspec:
2481                     clonespec.customization = self.customspec
2482 
2483                 if snapshot_src is not None:
2484                     if vm_obj.snapshot is None:
2485                         self.module.fail_json(msg="No snapshots present for virtual machine or template [%(template)s]" % self.params)
2486                     snapshot = self.get_snapshots_by_name_recursively(snapshots=vm_obj.snapshot.rootSnapshotList,
2487                                                                       snapname=snapshot_src)
2488                     if len(snapshot) != 1:
2489                         self.module.fail_json(msg='virtual machine "%(template)s" does not contain'
2490                                                   ' snapshot named "%(snapshot_src)s"' % self.params)
2491 
2492                     clonespec.snapshot = snapshot[0].snapshot
2493 
2494                 clonespec.config = self.configspec
2495                 clone_method = 'Clone'
2496                 try:
2497                     task = vm_obj.Clone(folder=destfolder, name=self.params['name'], spec=clonespec)
2498                 except vim.fault.NoPermission as e:
2499                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to clone virtual machine %s to folder %s "
2500                                               "due to permission issue: %s" % (self.params['name'],
2501                                                                                destfolder,
2502                                                                                to_native(e.msg)))
2503                 self.change_detected = True
2504             else:
2505                 # ConfigSpec require name for VM creation
2506                 self.configspec.name = self.params['name']
2507                 self.configspec.files = vim.vm.FileInfo(logDirectory=None,
2508                                                         snapshotDirectory=None,
2509                                                         suspendDirectory=None,
2510                                                         vmPathName="[" + datastore_name + "]")
2511 
2512                 clone_method = 'CreateVM_Task'
2513                 try:
2514                     task = destfolder.CreateVM_Task(config=self.configspec, pool=resource_pool)
2515                 except vmodl.fault.InvalidRequest as e:
2516                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to create virtual machine due to invalid configuration "
2517                                               "parameter %s" % to_native(e.msg))
2518                 except vim.fault.RestrictedVersion as e:
2519                     self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to create virtual machine due to "
2520                                               "product versioning restrictions: %s" % to_native(e.msg))
2521                 self.change_detected = True
2522             self.wait_for_task(task)
2523         except TypeError as e:
2524             self.module.fail_json(msg="TypeError was returned, please ensure to give correct inputs. %s" % to_text(e))
2525 
2526         if task.info.state == 'error':
2527             # https://kb.vmware.com/selfservice/microsites/search.do?language=en_US&cmd=displayKC&externalId=2021361
2528             # https://kb.vmware.com/selfservice/microsites/search.do?language=en_US&cmd=displayKC&externalId=2173
2529 
2530             # provide these to the user for debugging
2531             clonespec_json = serialize_spec(clonespec)
2532             configspec_json = serialize_spec(self.configspec)
2533             kwargs = {
2534                 'changed': self.change_applied,
2535                 'failed': True,
2536                 'msg': task.info.error.msg,
2537                 'clonespec': clonespec_json,
2538                 'configspec': configspec_json,
2539                 'clone_method': clone_method
2540             }
2541 
2542             return kwargs
2543         else:
2544             # set annotation
2545             vm = task.info.result
2546             if self.params['annotation']:
2547                 annotation_spec = vim.vm.ConfigSpec()
2548                 annotation_spec.annotation = str(self.params['annotation'])
2549                 task = vm.ReconfigVM_Task(annotation_spec)
2550                 self.wait_for_task(task)
2551                 if task.info.state == 'error':
2552                     return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'annotation'}
2553 
2554             if self.params['customvalues']:
2555                 vm_custom_spec = vim.vm.ConfigSpec()
2556                 self.customize_customvalues(vm_obj=vm, config_spec=vm_custom_spec)
2557                 task = vm.ReconfigVM_Task(vm_custom_spec)
2558                 self.wait_for_task(task)
2559                 if task.info.state == 'error':
2560                     return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'customvalues'}
2561 
2562             if self.params['wait_for_ip_address'] or self.params['wait_for_customization'] or self.params['state'] in ['poweredon', 'restarted']:
2563                 set_vm_power_state(self.content, vm, 'poweredon', force=False)
2564 
2565                 if self.params['wait_for_ip_address']:
2566                     wait_for_vm_ip(self.content, vm, self.params['wait_for_ip_address_timeout'])
2567 
2568                 if self.params['wait_for_customization']:
2569                     is_customization_ok = self.wait_for_customization(vm=vm, timeout=self.params['wait_for_customization_timeout'])
2570                     if not is_customization_ok:
2571                         vm_facts = self.gather_facts(vm)
2572                         return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'instance': vm_facts, 'op': 'customization'}
2573 
2574             vm_facts = self.gather_facts(vm)
2575             return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': False, 'instance': vm_facts}

2577     def get_snapshots_by_name_recursively(self, snapshots, snapname):
2578         snap_obj = []
2579         for snapshot in snapshots:
2580             if snapshot.name == snapname:
2581                 snap_obj.append(snapshot)
2582             else:
2583                 snap_obj = snap_obj + self.get_snapshots_by_name_recursively(snapshot.childSnapshotList, snapname)
2584         return snap_obj

2586     def reconfigure_vm(self):
2587         self.configspec = vim.vm.ConfigSpec()
2588         self.configspec.deviceChange = []
2589         # create the relocation spec
2590         self.relospec = vim.vm.RelocateSpec()
2591         self.relospec.deviceChange = []
2592         self.configure_guestid(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2593         self.configure_cpu_and_memory(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2594         self.configure_hardware_params(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2595         self.configure_disks(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2596         self.configure_network(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2597         self.configure_cdrom(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2598         self.customize_customvalues(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj, config_spec=self.configspec)
2599         self.configure_resource_alloc_info(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2600         self.configure_vapp_properties(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2601 
2602         if self.params['annotation'] and self.current_vm_obj.config.annotation != self.params['annotation']:
2603             self.configspec.annotation = str(self.params['annotation'])
2604             self.change_detected = True
2605 
2606         if self.params['resource_pool']:
2607             self.relospec.pool = self.get_resource_pool()
2608 
2609             if self.relospec.pool != self.current_vm_obj.resourcePool:
2610                 task = self.current_vm_obj.RelocateVM_Task(spec=self.relospec)
2611                 self.wait_for_task(task)
2612                 if task.info.state == 'error':
2613                     return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'relocate'}
2614 
2615         # Only send VMware task if we see a modification
2616         if self.change_detected:
2617             task = None
2618             try:
2619                 task = self.current_vm_obj.ReconfigVM_Task(spec=self.configspec)
2620             except vim.fault.RestrictedVersion as e:
2621                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to reconfigure virtual machine due to"
2622                                           " product versioning restrictions: %s" % to_native(e.msg))
2623             self.wait_for_task(task)
2624             if task.info.state == 'error':
2625                 return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'reconfig'}
2626 
2627         # Rename VM
2628         if self.params['uuid'] and self.params['name'] and self.params['name'] != self.current_vm_obj.config.name:
2629             task = self.current_vm_obj.Rename_Task(self.params['name'])
2630             self.wait_for_task(task)
2631             if task.info.state == 'error':
2632                 return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'rename'}
2633 
2634         # Mark VM as Template
2635         if self.params['is_template'] and not self.current_vm_obj.config.template:
2636             try:
2637                 self.current_vm_obj.MarkAsTemplate()
2638                 self.change_applied = True
2639             except vmodl.fault.NotSupported as e:
2640                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to mark virtual machine [%s] "
2641                                           "as template: %s" % (self.params['name'], e.msg))
2642 
2643         # Mark Template as VM
2644         elif not self.params['is_template'] and self.current_vm_obj.config.template:
2645             resource_pool = self.get_resource_pool()
2646             kwargs = dict(pool=resource_pool)
2647 
2648             if self.params.get('esxi_hostname', None):
2649                 host_system_obj = self.select_host()
2650                 kwargs.update(host=host_system_obj)
2651 
2652             try:
2653                 self.current_vm_obj.MarkAsVirtualMachine(**kwargs)
2654                 self.change_applied = True
2655             except vim.fault.InvalidState as invalid_state:
2656                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Virtual machine is not marked"
2657                                           " as template : %s" % to_native(invalid_state.msg))
2658             except vim.fault.InvalidDatastore as invalid_ds:
2659                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Converting template to virtual machine"
2660                                           " operation cannot be performed on the"
2661                                           " target datastores: %s" % to_native(invalid_ds.msg))
2662             except vim.fault.CannotAccessVmComponent as cannot_access:
2663                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to convert template to virtual machine"
2664                                           " as operation unable access virtual machine"
2665                                           " component: %s" % to_native(cannot_access.msg))
2666             except vmodl.fault.InvalidArgument as invalid_argument:
2667                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to convert template to virtual machine"
2668                                           " due to : %s" % to_native(invalid_argument.msg))
2669             except Exception as generic_exc:
2670                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to convert template to virtual machine"
2671                                           " due to generic error : %s" % to_native(generic_exc))
2672 
2673             # Automatically update VMware UUID when converting template to VM.
2674             # This avoids an interactive prompt during VM startup.
2675             uuid_action = [x for x in self.current_vm_obj.config.extraConfig if x.key == "uuid.action"]
2676             if not uuid_action:
2677                 uuid_action_opt = vim.option.OptionValue()
2678                 uuid_action_opt.key = "uuid.action"
2679                 uuid_action_opt.value = "create"
2680                 self.configspec.extraConfig.append(uuid_action_opt)
2681 
2682             self.change_detected = True
2683 
2684         # add customize existing VM after VM re-configure
2685         if 'existing_vm' in self.params['customization'] and self.params['customization']['existing_vm']:
2686             if self.current_vm_obj.config.template:
2687                 self.module.fail_json(msg="VM is template, not support guest OS customization.")
2688             if self.current_vm_obj.runtime.powerState != vim.VirtualMachinePowerState.poweredOff:
2689                 self.module.fail_json(msg="VM is not in poweroff state, can not do guest OS customization.")
2690             cus_result = self.customize_exist_vm()
2691             if cus_result['failed']:
2692                 return cus_result
2693 
2694         vm_facts = self.gather_facts(self.current_vm_obj)
2695         return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': False, 'instance': vm_facts}

2697     def customize_exist_vm(self):
2698         task = None
2699         # Find if we need network customizations (find keys in dictionary that requires customizations)
2700         network_changes = False
2701         for nw in self.params['networks']:
2702             for key in nw:
2703                 # We don't need customizations for these keys
2704                 if key not in ('device_type', 'mac', 'name', 'vlan', 'type', 'start_connected', 'dvswitch_name'):
2705                     network_changes = True
2706                     break
2707         if len(self.params['customization']) > 1 or network_changes or self.params.get('customization_spec'):
2708             self.customize_vm(vm_obj=self.current_vm_obj)
2709         try:
2710             task = self.current_vm_obj.CustomizeVM_Task(self.customspec)
2711         except vim.fault.CustomizationFault as e:
2712             self.module.fail_json(msg="Failed to customization virtual machine due to CustomizationFault: %s" % to_native(e.msg))
2713         except vim.fault.RuntimeFault as e:
2714             self.module.fail_json(msg="failed to customization virtual machine due to RuntimeFault: %s" % to_native(e.msg))
2715         except Exception as e:
2716             self.module.fail_json(msg="failed to customization virtual machine due to fault: %s" % to_native(e.msg))
2717         self.wait_for_task(task)
2718         if task.info.state == 'error':
2719             return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True, 'msg': task.info.error.msg, 'op': 'customize_exist'}
2720 
2721         if self.params['wait_for_customization']:
2722             set_vm_power_state(self.content, self.current_vm_obj, 'poweredon', force=False)
2723             is_customization_ok = self.wait_for_customization(vm=self.current_vm_obj, timeout=self.params['wait_for_customization_timeout'])
2724             if not is_customization_ok:
2725                 return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': True,
2726                         'msg': 'Wait for customization failed due to timeout', 'op': 'wait_for_customize_exist'}
2727 
2728         return {'changed': self.change_applied, 'failed': False}

2730     def wait_for_task(self, task, poll_interval=1):
2731         """
2732         Wait for a VMware task to complete.  Terminal states are 'error' and 'success'.
2733 
2734         Inputs:
2735           - task: the task to wait for
2736           - poll_interval: polling interval to check the task, in seconds
2737 
2738         Modifies:
2739           - self.change_applied
2740         """
2741         # https://www.vmware.com/support/developer/vc-sdk/visdk25pubs/ReferenceGuide/vim.Task.html
2742         # https://www.vmware.com/support/developer/vc-sdk/visdk25pubs/ReferenceGuide/vim.TaskInfo.html
2743         # https://github.com/virtdevninja/pyvmomi-community-samples/blob/master/samples/tools/tasks.py
2744         while task.info.state not in ['error', 'success']:
2745             time.sleep(poll_interval)
2746         self.change_applied = self.change_applied or task.info.state == 'success'
2747 
2748     def get_vm_events(self, vm, eventTypeIdList):
2749         byEntity = vim.event.EventFilterSpec.ByEntity(entity=vm, recursion="self")
2750         filterSpec = vim.event.EventFilterSpec(entity=byEntity, eventTypeId=eventTypeIdList)
2751         eventManager = self.content.eventManager
2752         return eventManager.QueryEvent(filterSpec)
2753 
2754     def wait_for_customization(self, vm, timeout=3600, sleep=10):
2755         poll = int(timeout // sleep)
2756         thispoll = 0
2757         while thispoll <= poll:
2758             eventStarted = self.get_vm_events(vm, ['CustomizationStartedEvent'])
2759             if len(eventStarted):
2760                 thispoll = 0
2761                 while thispoll <= poll:
2762                     eventsFinishedResult = self.get_vm_events(vm, ['CustomizationSucceeded', 'CustomizationFailed'])
2763                     if len(eventsFinishedResult):
2764                         if not isinstance(eventsFinishedResult[0], vim.event.CustomizationSucceeded):
2765                             self.module.warn("Customization failed with error {%s}:{%s}"
2766                                              % (eventsFinishedResult[0]._wsdlName, eventsFinishedResult[0].fullFormattedMessage))
2767                             return False
2768                         else:
2769                             return True
2770                     else:
2771                         time.sleep(sleep)
2772                         thispoll += 1
2773                 if len(eventsFinishedResult) == 0:
2774                     self.module.warn('Waiting for customization result event timed out.')
2775                     return False
2776             else:
2777                 time.sleep(sleep)
2778                 thispoll += 1
2779         if len(eventStarted):
2780             self.module.warn('Waiting for customization result event timed out.')
2781         else:
2782             self.module.warn('Waiting for customization start event timed out.')
2783         return False

2786 def main():
2787     argument_spec = vmware_argument_spec()
2788     argument_spec.update(

2790                    choices=['absent', 'poweredoff', 'poweredon', 'present', 'rebootguest', 'restarted', 'shutdownguest', 'suspended']),

2792         is_template=dict(type='bool', default=False),

2797         uuid=dict(type='str'),
2798         use_instance_uuid=dict(type='bool', default=False),
2799         folder=dict(type='str'),
2800         guest_id=dict(type='str'),
2801         disk=dict(type='list', default=[]),
2802         cdrom=dict(type=list_or_dict, default=[]),
2803         hardware=dict(type='dict', default={}),
2804         force=dict(type='bool', default=False),
2805         datacenter=dict(type='str', default='ha-datacenter'),
2806         esxi_hostname=dict(type='str'),
2807         cluster=dict(type='str'),
2808         wait_for_ip_address=dict(type='bool', default=False),
2809         wait_for_ip_address_timeout=dict(type='int', default=300),
2810         state_change_timeout=dict(type='int', default=0),
2811         snapshot_src=dict(type='str'),
2812         linked_clone=dict(type='bool', default=False),
2813         networks=dict(type='list', default=[]),
2814         resource_pool=dict(type='str'),
2815         customization=dict(type='dict', default={}, no_log=True),
2816         customization_spec=dict(type='str', default=None),
2817         wait_for_customization=dict(type='bool', default=False),
2818         wait_for_customization_timeout=dict(type='int', default=3600),
2819         vapp_properties=dict(type='list', default=[]),
2820         datastore=dict(type='str'),
2821         convert=dict(type='str', choices=['thin', 'thick', 'eagerzeroedthick']),
2822         delete_from_inventory=dict(type='bool', default=False),
2823     )
2824 
2825     module = AnsibleModule(argument_spec=argument_spec,
2826                            supports_check_mode=True,
2827                            mutually_exclusive=[
2828                                ['cluster', 'esxi_hostname'],
2829                            ],
2830                            required_one_of=[
2831                                ['name', 'uuid'],
2832                            ],
2833                            )
2834 
2835     result = {'failed': False, 'changed': False}
2836 
2837     pyv = PyVmomiHelper(module)
2838 
2839     # Check if the VM exists before continuing
2840     vm = pyv.get_vm()
2841 
2842     # VM already exists
2843     if vm:
2844         if module.params['state'] == 'absent':
2845             # destroy it
2846             if module.check_mode:
2847                 result.update(
2848                     vm_name=vm.name,
2849                     changed=True,
2850                     current_powerstate=vm.summary.runtime.powerState.lower(),
2851                     desired_operation='remove_vm',
2852                 )
2853                 module.exit_json(**result)
2854             if module.params['force']:
2855                 # has to be poweredoff first
2856                 set_vm_power_state(pyv.content, vm, 'poweredoff', module.params['force'])
2857             result = pyv.remove_vm(vm, module.params['delete_from_inventory'])
2858         elif module.params['state'] == 'present':
2859             if module.check_mode:
2860                 result.update(
2861                     vm_name=vm.name,
2862                     changed=True,
2863                     desired_operation='reconfigure_vm',
2864                 )
2865                 module.exit_json(**result)
2866             result = pyv.reconfigure_vm()
2867         elif module.params['state'] in ['poweredon', 'poweredoff', 'restarted', 'suspended', 'shutdownguest', 'rebootguest']:
2868             if module.check_mode:
2869                 result.update(
2870                     vm_name=vm.name,
2871                     changed=True,
2872                     current_powerstate=vm.summary.runtime.powerState.lower(),
2873                     desired_operation='set_vm_power_state',
2874                 )
2875                 module.exit_json(**result)
2876             # set powerstate
2877             tmp_result = set_vm_power_state(pyv.content, vm, module.params['state'], module.params['force'], module.params['state_change_timeout'])
2878             if tmp_result['changed']:
2879                 result["changed"] = True
2880                 if module.params['state'] in ['poweredon', 'restarted', 'rebootguest'] and module.params['wait_for_ip_address']:
2881                     wait_result = wait_for_vm_ip(pyv.content, vm, module.params['wait_for_ip_address_timeout'])
2882                     if not wait_result:
2883                         module.fail_json(msg='Waiting for IP address timed out')
2884                     tmp_result['instance'] = wait_result
2885             if not tmp_result["failed"]:
2886                 result["failed"] = False
2887             result['instance'] = tmp_result['instance']
2888             if tmp_result["failed"]:
2889                 result["failed"] = True
2890                 result["msg"] = tmp_result["msg"]
2891         else:
2892             # This should not happen
2893             raise AssertionError()
2894     # VM doesn't exist
2895     else:
2896         if module.params['state'] in ['poweredon', 'poweredoff', 'present', 'restarted', 'suspended']:
2897             if module.check_mode:
2898                 result.update(
2899                     changed=True,
2900                     desired_operation='deploy_vm',
2901                 )
2902                 module.exit_json(**result)
2903             result = pyv.deploy_vm()
2904             if result['failed']:
2905                 module.fail_json(msg='Failed to create a virtual machine : %s' % result['msg'])
2906 
2907     if result['failed']:
2908         module.fail_json(**result)
2909     else:
2910         module.exit_json(**result)
2911 
2912 
2913 if __name__ == '__main__':
2914     main()
